@waprin RE:

> Do I also use this in param docstrings? Below I also have a note in timeseries value docstring

Any note in a docstring can use the Sphinx directives (including `note`)

Somewhat orthogonal but this could be to use the [`request`](https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/reference.html#_pytest.fixtures.FixtureRequest.getfixturevalue) fixture to lazily request these fixtures:

```python
def the_test(request):
    if call_as_instance:
        contract = request.getfixturevalue('emitter')
    else:
        contract = request.getfixturevalue('Emitter')
```

It'd give us *some* increase in test speed since it won't need to deploy the `emitter` contract for every single run.
